# Copy to the repo root and fill in real values (never commit `.env`):
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The harness loads `.env` from `poc-eval-harness/` cwd or the parent directory
# (`BMAD-METHOD/.env`). Existing shell environment variables always win.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Agent — choose ONE configuration block
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Option A (recommended for local demo): Gemini OpenAI-compatible endpoint
GEMINI_API_KEY=
CURSOR_BASE_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/

# Option B: Cursor API bridge / custom OpenAI-compatible proxy
# CURSOR_API_KEY=
# CURSOR_BASE_URL=https://api.cursor.com/v1

# Option C: Direct Anthropic API (leave CURSOR_BASE_URL unset)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Simulator — batch eval campaigns only (FR-21: decorrelated from agent)
# Uses the same GEMINI_API_KEY (or GOOGLE_API_KEY) via google-genai.
# Not required for Streamlit demo or `harness.interactive` with synthetic profiles.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# GEMINI_API_KEY=   # uncomment if different from agent block above

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Stakeholder demo — Salesforce handover notes (PII; local path only)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Never commit the `.xlsx` export. Set an absolute path or place the file in
# ~/Downloads as "Notes for Tamar*.xlsx", or under poc-eval-harness/data/*.xlsx
#
# SALES_NOTES_XLSX=/absolute/path/to/Notes for Tamar-2026-06-02-13-51-50 (1).xlsx
